Quote: An Act to provide for the commemoration of the signing of the Treaty of Waitangi... 2. Waitangi Day - The sixth day of February in every year shall be known as Waitangi Day and shall be observed throughout New Zealand as a national day of thanksgiving in commemoration of the signing of the Treaty of Waitangi.
