Quote: WAITANGI DAY .. Tribute to the foresight and generosity of Lord and Lady Bledisloe in presenting Waitangi House to the people of New Zealand was paid by Mr. Cheviot Bell, president of the New Zealand Founders' Society, at a reception in the Majestic Cabaret last night.   The function, given to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the Treaty of Waitangi, was attended by the Mayor, Mr. T. C. A. Hislop, and Mrs. Hislop, and by Mr. R. A. Boulter, British Trade Commissioner.
